<HEADLINE> Wimbledon Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WIMBLEDON, England (AP) -- A brief look at what happened Thursday  
on the 10th day of the Wimbledon championships: 
</P>
<P>
	Weather -- Long periods of rain, which forced some matches to be  
suspended or postponed. High temperature was 68 degrees. 
</P>
<P>
	Attendance -- 30,223. Last year on the 10th day, the crowd was  
29,236. The record for the second Thursday is 31,724 in 1997. The 
total attendance so far is 364,248, an increase of 21,910 over last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Unfinished matches-- Men: No. 2 Patrick Rafter against No. 8 Todd  
Martin, No. 6 Tim Henman against Cedric Pioline. 
</P>
<P>
	Unplayed matches -- Men: No. 1 Pete Sampras against No. 7 Mark  
Philippoussis, No. 4. Andre Agassi against No. 11 Gustavo Kuerten. 
</P>
<P>
	Seeded winners -- Women: No. 2 Steffi Graf over No. 6 Venus  
Williams, No. 3 Lindsay Davenport over No. 5 Jana Novotna. 
</P>
<P>
	Unfinished matches -- Women: No. 8 Nathalie Tauziat against  
Mirjana Lucic, Jelena Dokic against Alexandra Stevenson. 
</P>
<P>
	Stat of the Day -- Because of rain delays, Steffi Graf's match  
against Venus Williams lasted 7 hours, 7 minutes, although actual 
playing time was 1:52. 
</P>
<P>
	Quote of the Day -- ``To get to the semis so far is huge, and to  
beat the best grass court player is a big win.'' - Lindsay 
Davenport, after beating defending champion Jana Novotna. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
