<HEADLINE> Hatch Files To Run for President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Sen. Orrin Hatch, R-Utah, officially became  
the latest candidate to enter the Republican presidential race, 
filing a statement of candidacy Thursday with the Federal Election 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
	By registering with the FEC, Hatch will be required to regularly  
disclose contributions and expenditures. Like many of the other GOP 
presidential hopefuls, however, Hatch is calling his campaign 
committee an ``exploratory committee.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Senate Judiciary Committee chairman announced last month  
that he would enter the presidential race. While acknowledging the 
strength of front-runner George W. Bush, Hatch said he wanted to be 
available in case the Texas governor stumbles. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not good to have a juggernaut in the party,'' Hatch said  
in a telephone interview Thursday. ``It's healthy to have some 
competition and I plan to provide that.'' 
  	   	
</P>
