<HEADLINE> Angels' Hill Has Elbow Re-Examined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Anaheim Angels pitcher Ken Hill, who  
underwent arthroscopic elbow surgery last summer, had his right 
elbow examined again Thursday and the team said following a CT scan 
that it will follow a conservative course of treatment. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill (3-7) allowed three runs and three hits in two innings in  
the Angels' 8-3 loss to Seattle on June 23. He did not come out to 
start the third inning because of a tight right elbow. It was his 
shortest appearance of the season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
