<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Watson Pharmaceutical, up 2 1/4 at 37 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Watson expects second-quarter earnings and revenue to be in line  
with market expectations. Several investment brokerages reiterated 
``buy'' ratings on the company, a maker of generic drugs. 

</P>
<P>
 *Walt Disney Co., down 1 13/16 at 29    	
</P>
<P>
	Morgan Stanley Dean Witter cut its earnings estimate for Disney,  
a day after Merrill Lynch lowered its expectations. An analyst 
cited weakened growth in ``creative content'' business lines, 
including consumer products licensing. 

</P>
<P>
 *Yankee Candle Co., priced at 18, closed at 24 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The maker of scented candles sold 12.5 million shares at $18  
apiece, raising $225 million in its initial public offering of 
stock. 

</P>
<P>
 *Lexford Residential Trust, down 3 13/16 at 20 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Lexford, a Reynoldsburg, Ohio, owner of apartment complexes,  
will be acquired by Equity Residential Properties Trust for $202.8 
million in stock, plus $530 million of assumed debt. The deal 
values Lexford below its Wednesday closing price. 

</P>
<P>
 *Amway Asia Pacific, up 1 5/8 at 13 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company said its business is in recovery, with strong  
momentum in China, improved sales in Malaysia and a lower level of 
sales declines in other markets. The company is the exclusive 
distribution vehicle for Amway Corp. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Starbucks Corp., down 10 5/8 at 26 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The gourmet coffee retailer said it expects to earn 54 cents per  
share in fiscal year 1999, compared to 60 cents per share forecast 
by analysts. Starbucks said it expects to miss estimates by 3 cents 
per share over the next two quarters. 

</P>
<P>
 *Books-A-Million, up 6 11/32 at 13 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The retailer will be the exclusive provider of books and related  
products to Wal-Mart's online customers. Books-A-Million, now the 
No. 3 U.S. book retailer, will also provide Internet order 
fulfillment services. 

</P>
<P>
 *Lycos Inc., up 10 1/2 at 102 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Lycos signed an electronic-commerce agreement with Bank One  
Corp.'s WingspanBank.com that could generate up to $135 million in 
revenue for Lycos. The deal will allow Lycos users to handle most 
financial transactions online. 

</P>
<P>
 *S3 Inc., up 2 5/32 at 11 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The graphics chip maker said it will post second-quarter  
earnings somewhere between a loss of 5 cents a share to break-even. 
Wall Street had expected S3 to lose 20 cents a share. 

</P>
<P>
 *RealNetworks Inc., up 9 at 77 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company will provide technology for WebTV Networks to  
upgrade its products to be able to support certain audio formats. 
RealNetworks will also develop a new device for use in a Windows 
operating platform. 


  	   	
</P>
