<HEADLINE> Ex-Diplomat Leaves Dog in Lincoln </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BETHESDA, M.D. (AP) -- Jeane Kirkpatrick may be in the dog house  
with animal lovers after locking her poodle in her car during a 
sweltering summer day. 
</P>
<P>
	The former ambassador to the United Nations under President  
Reagan apparently left her dog Jasper in her Lincoln Continental 
with the windows rolled up as she shopped Saturday at some 
boutiques. Temperatures rose into the 90s. 
</P>
<P>
	A police officer issued Ms. Kirkpatrick a $45 ticket for  
violating a state law which forbids leaving animals in locked cars. 
</P>
<P>
	Sharon Kessler, executive director of the Montgomery County  
Humane Society, said Ms. Kirkpatrick probably didn't know the 
dangers of leaving a dog in a locked car on a hot day. 
</P>
<P>
	``The animal can die within a very few minutes,'' she said.  
</P>
<P>
	A spokeswoman for Ms. Kirkpatrick at the American Enterprise  
Institute, where she is a senior fellow, did not return a call for 
comment Wednesday. 
  	   	
</P>
