<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Olympic Airways Hit by Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATHENS, Greece (AP) -- More than half of Olympic Airways flights  
were grounded Thursday as employees staged a strike in protest of a 
management handover to a subsidiary of British Airways. 
</P>
<P>
	At least 46 of the 77 planned flights were canceled by the labor  
action at the troubled national carrier during the peak tourism 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Unions at Olympic called the strike after Speedwing, a  
subsidiary of British Airways, took over management in a bid to 
turn around the money-losing airline. 
</P>
<P>
	According to the agreement, Speedwing will run Olympic for 30  
months, overseeing a financial rescue plan for the airline long 
plagued by debts and labor disputes. British Airways will be 
allowed to buy a stake in the airline of up to 20 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The government argues Olympic cannot survive unless it forms  
partnerships with major airlines and insists the deal will not lead 
to job losses. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
