<HEADLINE> Ex-Wife Gets $22M in Divorce Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The ex-wife of Warner LeRoy, owner of the posh  
Tavern on the Green, will still be able to eat at the finest 
restaurants thanks to a $22 million-plus divorce settlement. 
</P>
<P>
	A judge Wednesday granted Kay LeRoy $15 million, a house in Long  
Island worth about $5.5 million, art by Picasso and Monet and 
$65,000 a month for the rest of her life, her lawyer David Aronson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Justice Walter Tolub, who presided over the bitter divorce trial  
last year, gave Mrs. LeRoy about 40 percent of the $47 million 
marital estate. 
</P>
<P>
	``They got substantially less in legal fees than they asked  
for,'' said LeRoy's lawyer, Jeffrey Cohen. ``There are substantial 
issues to be determined on appeal.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The LeRoys married in 1970 and had three children, all of whom  
are now in their 20s. LeRoy, 63, is a descendant of the movie 
moguls who started Warner Bros. Studios. 
  	   	
