<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Final 4 Set in European Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- Spain, led by Alberto Herreros' 28 points, upset  
Lithuania 74-72 Thursday, earning a semifinal berth against France 
in the European Championships. 
</P>
<P>
	France, sparked by late heroics from Laurent Foirest, reached  
the final four with a 66-63 victory over Turkey. 
</P>
<P>
	Vlado Scepanovic came off the bench to score 17 points as  
two-time defending champion Yugoslavia beat Germany 78-68 to set up 
a semifinal game against Italy. 
</P>
<P>
	Carlton Myers scored 22 points and forward Gregor Fucka added  
19, leading Italy past Russia 102-79. 
</P>
<P>
	By reaching the semifinals, Italy, France and Spain also  
qualified for next year's Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
	Russia, silver medalists at last year's worlds, Germany, Turkey  
and Lithuania can still qualify for the Olympics in playoffs among 
losing quarterfinalists. Germany will play Russia, while Turkey 
will meet Lithuania, and the winners will qualify. 
</P>
<P>
	The top five teams, plus Yugoslavia, qualify for the Olympics.  
Yugoslavia qualified by winning the World Championships last year. 
</P>
<P>
	With Lithuanian center Arvydas Sabonis in early foul trouble,  
Spain led in a close game. Sabonis got his fourth foul with 16:44 
left. He returned seven minutes later, but fouled out seconds 
later. 
</P>
<P>
	Spain led by 10 with less than five minutes remaining, but  
3-point goals by Sarunas Jasikevicius and Arturas Karnisovas cut 
the lead. 
</P>
<P>
	With 18 seconds remaining, Karnisovas nailed another 3, tying  
the score 72-72. Alberto Anguilo hit two free throws with 11.1 
seconds left. With time running out, Jasikevicius, who led 
Lithuania with 22 points, missed a jumper. 
</P>
<P>
	Karnisovas had 17 points, while Sabonis had only three and three  
rebounds in 16 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Yugoslavia's defense, anchored by Vlade Divac, limited Germany's  
Dirk Nowitzki to 11 points. Drazan Tomic, who scored a 
tournament-high 32 points in Germany's victory over Croatia, was 
held to four. 
</P>
<P>
	Patrick Femerling led Germany with 13 points.  
</P>
<P>
	Italy, silver medalist behind Yugoslavia at the Europeans two  
years ago, overwhelmed Russia with tough defense and good outside 
shooting. 
</P>
<P>
	Vasily Karassev led Russia with 22 points, hitting 5-of-7 from  
3-point range. 
</P>
<P>
	France trailed Turkey most of the game until Foirest hit a  
3-pointer with 1:02 left for a 61-59 lead. He then converted a 
Turkish turnover for another basket. 
</P>
<P>
	Frederic Weis, the French center drafted by the New York Knicks,  
played less than four minutes and missed one shot. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
