<HEADLINE> Calif. Rep. Brown Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Rep. George Brown, D-Calif., has been  
hospitalized since early June for treatment of an infection 
following heart valve replacement surgery, his office said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's being treated with antibiotics and he's getting better  
every day, but the course of treatment can take some weeks,'' said 
an aide, Bobi Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
	A spokeswoman at Bethesda Naval Hospital in suburban Maryland  
said no information was immediately available on his condition. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Johnson said Brown had been recovering from ``routine heart  
valve replacement surgery'' on May 3, and had made one or two trips 
to his office. 
</P>
<P>
	She said he re-entered the hospital during the first week of  
June for treatment of the infection. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown, 79, is serving his 18th term in the House and is the  
senior Democrat on the Science Committee. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
