<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tide Decides Not To Renew With Rudd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- One of the most familiar sites at a  
NASCAR track -- Ricky Rudd driving a Ford with a Tide logo painted 
on it -- will be history after this year, the company said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Procter &AMP; Gamble's announcement of the end of the nine-year  
relationship took Rudd by surprise and severely hindered his 
efforts to build a multi-car racing team. 
</P>
<P>
	Procter &AMP; Gamble is negotiating to take its sponsorship to  
Precision Preparation Inc., a racing company owned by Cal Wells, 
whose primary racing interest is in the CART series. 
</P>
<P>
	P&AMP;G offered Rudd an opportunity to drive the PPI car, but he  
declined. 
</P>
<P>
	``Here's a guy who walks off with my sponsor, and they say, `Do  
you want to drive for him?,' Rudd said. ``That conversation didn't 
last very long.'' 
</P>
<P>
	At an impromptu news conference, Rudd tried to act like a good  
sport, but it was clear this blow hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think there's something wrong when you allow someone who  
isn't part of this sport to walk out with one of the biggest 
sponsors,'' Rudd said. 
</P>
<P>
	Tide spokeswoman Molly Humbert said it was a bittersweet moment  
for the company, one it hoped to avoid by offering Rudd a chance to 
drive for the new team. 
</P>
<P>
	``We looked at a lot of different opportunities including Ricky,  
both in terms of him being an owner and him being a driver,'' 
Humbert said. ``We feel we're moving in a good direction with 
PPI.'' 
</P>
<P>
	That company already has a sponsorship deal with McDonalds to  
run a car on the Busch series in 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, Rudd will go in search of a new sponsor for the  
Winston Cup team he formed in 1994. 
</P>
<P>
	He finished fifth in the point standings that year, but hasn't  
seriously contended since, due to rising costs and limited manpower 
in an era of burgeoning multi-car teams. He said his plans to add a 
second car will be put on hold. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite the problems, Rudd still holds the modern record for  
consecutive years with a victory, a stretch of 16 years from 
1983-98. 
</P>
<P>
	This year, he sits 38th in the points standings and hasn't  
finished in the top 10. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'd say 120 percent of my attention has been going to trying  
to make this team better,'' Rudd said. ``I used to see all the 
other stuff as trivial. But maybe it's not that trivial because 
they made a fancy presentation and now we don't have a sponsor.'' 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
