<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Crary Joining AP's National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- David Crary, bureau chief for The Associated  
Press in Toronto, has been named a member of AP's national 
reporting team based in New York. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced today by Mike Silverman, deputy  
managing editor for national news. 
</P>
<P>
	Crary, 48, joined the AP in 1976 in Jackson, Miss. He has been a  
foreign correspondent since 1985, serving in Nairobi, Kenya; as 
news editor in Johannesburg, South Africa, and Paris; and as bureau 
chief for Canada since 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Crary, a native of New Haven, Conn., has a bachelor's degree  
from Yale and a masters from Columbia University School of 
Journalism. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining the AP he worked for the now-defunct Hartford,  
Conn., Times. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
