<HEADLINE> Three Free Agents Stay with Sharks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Goalie Mike Vernon, defenseman Bill  
Houlder and right wing Tony Granato have decided to remain with San 
Jose Sharks, signing up for option years rather than pursuing free 
agency. 
</P>
<P>
	Vernon, a Stanley Cup winner with both the Calgary Flames and  
Detroit Red Wings, posted a 16-22-10 record with a 2.27 
goals-against average in 49 games last season. He holds the team's 
career shutout mark with nine and is third in career wins among 
active goalies with 347. 
</P>
<P>
	Houlder has scored 64 points -- 16 goals and 48 assists -- in 158  
games for the Sharks. and 203 points -- 50 goals and 153 assists -- 
in 530 NHL games. 
</P>
<P>
	Granato is tied for 16th on the Sharks all-time scoring list  
with 77 points -- 47 goals and 30 assists -- in 170 games since 
joining the team in August of 1996. He returned to the NHL after 
missing the final 32 games of the 1995-1996 season while recovering 
from brain surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sharks also announced they picked up the option on the  
contract of right wing Ronnie Stern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
