<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cubs' Gonzalez To Have Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Chicago Cubs right-hander Jeremi Gonzalez will  
have surgery in Los Angeles on Friday, his second elbow operation 
in 11 months. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Lewis Yocum repaired a ligament in the elbow and transposed  
the ulnar nerve last August. He will operate again. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez, 24, was 0-1 with a 2.52 ERA in eight rehabilitation  
starts this year at Single-A Daytona, Double-A West Tennessee and 
Triple-A Iowa. An MRI last month showed abnormalities. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez was 7-7 with a 5.32 ERA in 20 starts for the Cubs last  
season and has a 18-16 career record with a 4.71 ERA. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
