<HEADLINE> Ravens Sign WR Eric Metcalf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- Eric Metcalf, a wide receiver and running back  
who holds the NFL record with 11 kick-return touchdowns, agreed to 
terms Thursday with the Baltimore Ravens. 
</P>
<P>
	Metcalf, 31, an 11-year veteran, played under Ravens owner Art  
Modell with the Cleveland Browns before the franchise relocated to 
Baltimore. 
</P>
<P>
	Eric Matcalf, son of former Pro Bowl selection Terry Metcalf,  
played last season with Arizona. He had 31 receptions for 324 yard 
and brought back 43 punts for 295 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	Metcalf didn't score a touchdown last season, but in the season  
finale, he returned a kickoff 46 yards setting up the game-winning 
field goal in a victory that sent Arizona to the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	Metcalf has returned punts and kickoffs a combined 16,280 yards,  
an NFL record. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
