<HEADLINE> Best Buy, Prodigy Offer Rebates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Electronics retailer Best Buy and Internet  
service provider Prodigy Communications are teaming for a promotion 
targeting consumers who haven't yet bought personal computers. 
</P>
<P>
	They're offering rebates of up to $400 on purchase of a new PC  
with Prodigy Internet Service. 
</P>
<P>
	Prodigy says the effect could be to make entry level PCs free.  
</P>
<P>
	The Wall Street Journal reports the online service leader,  
America Online, is planning a similar promotion. 
</P>
<P>
	About half of U.S. homes have personal computers. Of those,  
about half are logging on to the Internet. 

  	   	
