<HEADLINE> Rodriguez MRI Shows No Damage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- An MRI test of Texas Rangers catcher  
Ivan Rodriguez's injured knee showed no damage Thursday, and the 
team said he could be in the lineup for Friday's game. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez, who apparently hyperextended his knee while running  
the bases during Texas' 18-4 victory over Anaheim on Wednesday 
night, was examined by team orthopedist Dr. John Conway. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez was diagnosed with a bone bruise on his left knee. A  
statement from the team said there was ``a good possibility'' he 
will be able to play against Seattle on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez is batting .308 with 13 home runs and 46 RBIs this  
season. 
  	   	
</P>
