<HEADLINE> Country Singer Is Cancer Free </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Ray Stevens, who wrote ``The Streak''  
and ``Everything Is Beautiful,'' says he's cancer-free after 
prostate surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	The 60-year-old singer had surgery June 15 at Johns Hopkins  
University Medical Center in Baltimore to remove his prostate. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm very fortunate to have been given a clean bill of health  
following my surgery,'' he said in a statement today. ``The cancer 
was confined to the prostate.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ray returns to the stage at the Acuff Theatre in Nashville on  
Sept. 15. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
