<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Albright Takes Unannounced Vacation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is away  
on vacation, without announcement and with her interim spokesman 
saying he had no ``information on her whereabouts.'' 
</P>
<P>
	James Foley, who is substituting for James P. Rubin, who also is  
on vacation, did tell reporters Thursday that Albright was expected 
to be back on the job in 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
	The daily schedule issued by the State Department press office  
listed Albright as having ``no public appointments.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Questioned by reporters, Foley said he was ``confirming to you  
now that she's on personal leave.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
