<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela Finance Minister Replaced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) -- Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez has  
replaced his finance minister, the seventh member of his cabinet to 
depart since he took office in February. 
</P>
<P>
	Maritza Izaguirre is out and the post will be filled by her  
35-year-old deputy Jose Rojas, Chavez told reporters late 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Izaguirre, 60, says she is leaving to return to her post at the  
Inter-American Development Bank in Washington, D.C. She was named 
finance minister last year by then-President Rafael Caldera and 
agreed to stay on temporarily to provide a transition between the 
administrations. 
</P>
<P>
	Izaguirre was among the more highly regarded members of Chavez's  
economic team, which critics say has lacked a coherent plan to 
bring the country out of one of its worst recessions in years. 
</P>
<P>
	Venezuela's economy plunged into a recession last year after  
prices for oil, the country's main export, fell to a 12-year low. 
The economy shrank by 9.8 percent between January and March this 
year, the fiscal deficit is $8 billion and unemployment is up to 15 
percent, according to official figures. 
</P>
<P>
	Five of the other cabinet members who resigned quit to run in  
elections July 25 for a constituent assembly that is to rewrite 
Venezuela's constitution -- the centerpiece of Chavez's governing 
agenda. 
</P>
<P>
	Izaguirre's departure could add to tensions in Venezuela.  
</P>
<P>
	Chavez, the leader of a failed 1992 coup attempt, is under  
attack by opponents for breaking campaign laws, naming scores of 
soldiers to government posts and allegedly planning to use the 
constituent assembly to impose authoritarian rule by temporarily 
shutting down Congress and the Supreme Court. 
</P>
<P>
	However, the former army paratrooper is also wildly popular  
among millions of poor people who think he will attack rampant 
political corruption blamed for squandering the country's vast oil 
wealth. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
