<HEADLINE> Packers Expect 10,000 at Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- The Green Bay Packers expect between  
10,000 and 12,000 of the team's owners to attend Wednesday's 
outdoor shareholders meeting at Lambeau Field. 
</P>
<P>
	The Packers are the nation's only publicly-owned sports team,  
and last year's meeting, the first of its kind, attracted 18,707 of 
the team's more than 100,000 shareholders. 
</P>
<P>
	Team president Bob Harlan, general manager Ron Wolf and other  
team officials will speak at Wednesday's meeting. Harlan will give 
an update on the team's pursuit of a new stadium, and Wolf will 
make his second ``State of the Team'' address. 
</P>
<P>
	Additional reports will be presented by the investment committee  
and the corporate marketing committee. The Packers also will elect 
15 directors to three-year terms. 
</P>
<P>
	Following the presentations, shareholders will be able to ask  
questions of the team officials. Last year's meeting featured a 
spirited discussion about then-unsigned running backs Dorsey Levens 
and Raymont Harris, both of whom eventually signed with the 
Packers. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
